The paper deals with algorithms for finding perfect matchings in bipartite graphs, which is a classic problem in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on regular bipartite graphs and presents an algorithm that achieves an expected running time of O(n^1.5) or O(m) depending on the input size. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): This sub-category deals with the design and analysis of algorithms and data structures, which is the main focus of the paper. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): This sub-category deals with mathematical structures and techniques that are relevant to computer science, such as graph theory and combinatorics, which are central to the paper. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): This sub-category deals with algorithms and data structures for solving geometric problems, which can be relevant to graph problems such as finding matchings. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): This sub-category deals with the study of the intrinsic difficulty of computational problems, which can be relevant to analyzing the running time of algorithms for finding matchings. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): This sub-category deals with the intersection of computer science and game theory, which can be relevant to analyzing the behavior of algorithms in strategic settings such as matching markets
